name: showansi
date: 20240306
comment: display ANSI art in a terminal
version: v%%VERSION%%
license: BSD 2-clause (all rights reserved)
author: Felix Palmen <felix@palmen-it.de>
description:
%%name%% combines dos2ansi with a terminal emulator (by default xterm) and a
pager (by default less) to form an ANSI-art viewer.
.
defgroup: 2

[flag V]
group: 0
optional: 0
description: Print version information and exit.

[flag S]
description:
Ignore SAUCE and other metadata and use all defaults.

Also passes ignoring SAUCE to dos2ansi.
.

[flag c columns]
description:
The number of columns for display, IOW, the width of the terminal window.

Also passed to dos2ansi as the default canvas width (-w).
.

[flag d dos2ansi]
description:
Run %%arg%% to render the input file for the configured pager to display.
.
default: %%DOS2ANSI%%

[flag e]
description: Use an EGA font by default.
default: Default to using a VGA font.

[flag h]
group: 1
optional: 0
description: Print a help text and exit.

[flag n]
description: Disable letter spacing by default.

[flag r rows]
description:
The number of rows for display, IOW, the height of the terminal window.
.

[flag s]
description: Assume square pixels by default.

[flag w]
description: Use a wide font (VGA50 or EGA43) by default.

[arg args]
description:
Arguments for dos2ansi, including the file to display. Must be preceded by
'--' if it contains flags (starting with '-'). If it doesn't contain a file
to display, the standard input will be read and fed to dos2ansi.
.

